    "description": "<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When you see a creature belonging to the </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>beast</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">, </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>monster</strong>, </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">or </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>plant </strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Species cast a spell, you may immediately choose to learn that spell as a Chimerist spell of your own: if you do, record the </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Species </strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">of the creature you learned it from.</span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When you first acquire this Skill, choose </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>【</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>INS + WLP</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>】 </strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">or </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>【</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>MIG + WLP</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>】</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">. From now on, your offensive </span>( <strong>@ICON[offensive]</strong> ) <span class=\"fontstyle0\">Chimerist spells will use the chosen Attributes for the Magic Check, regardless of the Attributes used by the creature you learned the spell from.</span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You may have </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>up to </strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>【</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>SL + 2</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>】</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>different Chimerist spells</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">memorized this way. If you want to memorize a new Chimerist spell but are already at your limit, you must forget one of your old spells and replace it with the new spell.</span> </p>",
